error.description: At least one object describing a failure. If a queue sharing group is involved, the objects will specify the queue managers on which the operation failed.

success.description: Only produced if a queue sharing group is involved and the operation failed on at least one queue manager. The entries in the array identify queue managers on which the operation succeeded.

permitStandby.description: (not available on z/OS, or the MQ Appliance)

correlationId.description: 48 character hex-string representing the correlation ID.

messageId.description: 48 character hex-string representing the message ID.

messageFormat.description: Message format corresponding to the MQMD field.

type.description: Type of error, for example "rest" meaning an error in the REST API itself.

msgId.description: A unique identifier for the error category.

message.description: An explanatory message describing the problem.

explanation.description: A more detailed message describing the problem.

action.description: An outline of how the user could avoid the problem.

qmgrName.description: The name of queue manager on which the operation failed, only returned for errors in queue sharing group operations.

completioncode.description: The MQ completion code associated with the failure - 0 (MQCC_OK) if not applicable.

reasonCode.description: The MQ reason code associated with the failure - 0 (MQRC_NONE) if not applicable.
